<p><persName>J. H. Bell </persName>                                <date when="1824-07-25">25th July 1824</date></p>

<p>To <persName>Buckner and Powel</persName> Dr</p>
<p>This sum in Cash_______________________________________________$25. 00
1 Phial Laudanum_________________________________75cts \
1 do Balsam______________________________________75    |  ___    2. 25
1   do   Penny  Royal____________________________75    /
30 lbs Nails 25 cts____________________________________________  7. 50
										     _______
By                                                             $34. 75

2 Doz  Buttons_________________________________________________  4.
										    ________
Balance due____________________________________________________$30. 75</p>

<p><persName>Mr. Bell</persName> you will please pay to <persName>Colo Austin</persName> or order the above
account and oblidge yours respectfully</p>

<p><persName>Aylett C. Buckner</persName></p>

<p><persName>Mr. J. H. Bell</persName></p>

<p>N. B.   The $25 to be paid in cash
the balance in trade           </p>

<p>NB.</p>

<p>If you made use of the horse which you recd at twenty dollars in
any way that might have caused his death I shall expect you to pay
me that amt but if you merely wrode him home to your <placeName>house </placeName>and did
not use him afterwards I am willing to sustain the loss though I am
in no ways bound to do so neither am I under any obligations to
sustain the loss                                              </p>

<p><persName>Aylett C. Buckner</persName></p>

<p><persName>J. H. Bell</persName></p>

<p><date when="1824-07-25">25th July 1824</date></p>


